= xml:Tailor - XML Tag Attribute Language for Ruby

Copyright (c) 2002 Thomas Sawyer, LGPL

== Introduction

xml:Tailor is a TAL, a Tag Attribute Language, for Ruby. What is a TAL?
TALs are like template systems for SGML derivitives (XML/XHTML),
but more powerful, and rather compare to ERuby.
The advantage of a TALs, though, 
is that you can use standard visual HTML editors without difficulty.
This is due to all dynamic markup is specified in attributes
rather than as special tags.

== Installation

To install xml:Tailor simply unpack the gzipped tarball into your local site_ruby path.
This path is usually +/usr/local/lib/site_ruby/1.6/+.
An install script is not currently provided.

== Requirements

REXML 2.3.5+|
TomsLib::REREXML

== Usage

Currently you'll just have to weed through the example and code.

